The paper deals with problems related to geometric structures and combinatorial optimization, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of lower and upper bounds, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in the context of generalizations of crossing families. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CG and cs.DM, followed by cs.DS, cs.GT, and cs.CC.
